This commit refactors the entire project from JavaScript to TypeScript to improve type safety and maintainability. It also adds comments to the code to improve clarity.

Changes include:
- Added TypeScript and type definitions for React, Leaflet, and Node.
- Created `tsconfig.json` and `tsconfig.node.json` for TypeScript configuration.
- Renamed all `.jsx` files to `.tsx`.
- Updated `index.html` to point to the new `.tsx` entry point.
- Refactored all components (`App`, `Map`, `ChangeView`) to use TypeScript, adding types for props, state, and function signatures.
- Added JSDoc comments to all components and key functions to explain their purpose and logic.
- Added comments to the Vite configuration file and renamed it to `vite.config.ts`.
